---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="About" description="About b4rt and dumpthecore — a developer blog about Linux, systems, and debugging.">
  <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    About
  </h1>

  <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none">
    <p>
      Hey — I'm <strong>b4rt</strong>. I work on systems software: Linux kernel internals, embedded devices, networking stacks, and the kind of code that runs quietly until it doesn't.
    </p>

    <p>
      This blog is called <strong>dumpthecore</strong> because when a process crashes hard enough, the OS writes a core dump — a raw snapshot of everything at the moment of failure. That's the aesthetic here: raw, unfiltered notes on things I've built, debugged, and occasionally destroyed.
    </p>

    <h2>What I write about</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Linux internals</strong> — scheduling, memory, syscalls, eBPF</li>
      <li><strong>Debugging</strong> — profilers, tracers, sanitizers, the whole toolkit</li>
      <li><strong>Systems design</strong> — how distributed systems actually work</li>
      <li><strong>C and Rust</strong> — the languages where mistakes are interesting</li>
      <li><strong>Tools</strong> — anything that makes me faster or less wrong</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The setup</h2>
    <p>
      This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro 5</a> and MDX. Content lives in git.
      No CMS, no database, no JavaScript unless it's earning its place.
      Hosted on Cloudflare Pages.
    </p>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>
    <p>
      No social media. If you want to reach me, the best way is through the content — write about something I wrote, link to it, and I'll probably find it. Or open an issue on whatever I've broken.
    </p>

    <p>
      Subscribe via <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a> — it's the only feed that matters.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
